		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Sacramento</placeName> <date>March 4&#47;1856</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>&#33;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir&#33;</p>
				<p>Enclosed you will find some<lb/> resolutions&#44; which have been<lb/> <sic>handet</sic> to me to forward to<lb/> you.  You will address the three<lb/> copies of the Occident to <persName>S. Hoffman</persName><lb/> It grieves me to bring to notice<lb/> again that the Jewish Citizen<lb/> here are so neglecting as not even<lb/> to come to &#40;minyan&#41; on <date><sic>Sabath</sic></date><lb/> and would it not be for a few<lb/> which exert themselves&#44; <sic>their</sic><lb/> would be <sic>non</sic> at all&#44; and what<lb/> is the reason money their god<lb/> it would please me greatly if you <lb/>would make a few remarks in<lb/> the Occident in <sic>regart</sic> to it.</p>
				<p>The Occident is received here now<lb/> regularly and all parties are<lb/> satisfied with it&#44; as we like independent<lb/> Papers.  Your agent <persName>I. Greenebaum</persName><lb/> is going to leave here on a trip</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>to the states on the <date>20<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> of this<lb/> hoping that this will reach<lb/> you in good health and<lb/> accept the best wishes of your friend</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">N. Hoshland</persName></p>
				<p>NB  If it should require a signature<lb/> to the communication in regard<lb/> to the jewish nos coming to the<lb/> synagogue. please and sign it &#40;<persName>N.</persName>&#41;</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><del><add>&#63;</add></del></p>
		</body>
